(30130,'Narcissism Test',2,215,'Constantly craving attention and admiration, narcissistic individuals believe they are superior to others. While self-esteem and confidence are healthy, severe narcissism may tip into a personality disorder. Take this test to learn where you fall on the spectrum. Using the key below, answer the questions based on how strongly you agree or disagree with the statement. This test is for anyone who wants to explore their level of narcissism. It’s designed for adults and is not intended to be diagnostic. If you think you struggle with narcissism, seeking the help of a therapist can be beneficial. Find a professional near you in the Psychology Today Therapy Directory. Back, M.D., et al. Narcissistic Admiration and Rivalry Questionnaire (NARQ). Raskin, R. and Terry, H. Narcissistic Personality Inventory (NPI). Schoenleber, M. et al. Brief Pathological Narcissism Inventory (B-PNI).','[-0.03427518,0.06772005,-0.0433287,0.012788527,-0.07188293,-0.03144485,0.012622266,0.043292377,-0.031372476,0.040277284,0.122089885,-0.042491283,-0.03151656,-0.008610796,0.02746379,0.023136768,0.0033736017,0.006608896,-0.10297517,-0.055115093,-0.026686495,-0.0063265865,-0.017639894,0.029588584,-0.034028776,0.03325084,0.03869593,-0.079309,0.13204585,-0.07235663,0.10213998,0.11740655,0.022145811,-0.02694973,-0.019397931,0.070203885,-0.0032881903,-0.052966293,0.009643339,-0.012395151,0.025798984,-0.08687139,-0.01464109,-0.08881132,0.058297493,-0.033514377,-0.08926324,0.0056686183,0.052592836,0.0050930064,-0.052346773,0.007889374,0.019103419,-0.05443157,0.012095116,-0.09188153,-0.024562744,0.04450079,0.013696141,0.0037318757,-0.010905034,0.023080442,0.020181984,-0.0015141062,0.052070923,-0.01684337,-0.050804805,-0.026847212,-0.033259075,0.039342776,0.060012218,-0.08798494,-0.008540331,0.05192856,-0.10175023,-0.06556762,0.011972024,0.014286312,-0.0019062079,-0.0075446083,0.050163396,0.048740894,0.019577328,0.0034195397,-0.1108758,-0.04077045,-0.036230575,-0.0007291204