(30132,'Psychopathy Test',2,217,'Psychopathy is a personality trait characterized by a lack of empathy, blunted emotions, and manipulative, callous behavior; someone high in psychopathy may be diagnosed with antisocial personality disorder, a related condition. Take this test to see where you fall on the psychopathy spectrum. Using the key below, answer the questions based on how strongly you agree or disagree with the statement. This test is for anyone interested in assessing themselves for signs of psychopathy. This test is designed for adults and is not intended to be diagnostic; a high score does not mean you are a psychopath. If you are concerned about a tendency toward antisocial or uncaring behavior, make an appointment with a licensed mental health provider; you can find one in your area on the Psychology Today Therapy Directory.','[-0.018447177,0.021640597,-0.0018666686,-0.013740258,-0.053678103,0.008120224,0.049845017,0.079813525,-0.033607993,0.010138042,0.07083466,0.0020282299,-0.00845596,-0.027858878,-0.07505423,-0.003554909,0.0147316,-0.058359664,-0.030463286,0.032715574,-0.018901015,0.006038956,-0.0356494,0.00953053,-0.0585004,0.030238966,-0.023342645,-0.088884,0.119947396,0.05290816,0.06066882,0.10781595,-0.025848724,-0.029403433,-0.0028710968,0.027268695,-0.05277765,0.06347581,-0.012568127,0.026397066,-0.0028478904,-0.076401755,-0.064750336,-0.057645775,0.07650845,-0.054753896,-0.10735092,0.021210598,0.06656339,-0.03571831,-0.14694169,-0.041002177,0.011060886,0.07180773,-0.0038835108,-0.11188444,0.027710821,0.020184701,-0.068425074,-0.039360587,-0.029955892,0.028925125,0.07882363,-0.0151097495,0.08775477,0.03609829,-0.006132434,-0.038388975,0.05577737,0.024427846,0.039130934,-0.023070978,0.06219459,0.08195691,-0.09895522,0.007334407,-0.0071357707,-0.01360572,-0.016073681,0.038692817,0.020233179,0.03465219,0.04763517,0.018112138,-0.01421159,-0.0026034103,-0.05083594,0.009885476,-0.040260546,-0.015451884,0.03733642,0.030937223,-0.042308487,-0.08597246,