(30225,'Schizophrenia',2,300,'Schizophrenia can be a frightening diagnosis, but it’s not hopeless. With the right medication, therapy, and support, many people with schizophrenia are able to control their symptoms, be independent, and lead rich, fulfilling lives. Overcoming challenges with a loved one, while also taking care of yourself Recognizing schizophrenia and getting help What you can do to manage symptoms and support recovery Coping with addiction and a mental health problem How it works and how to decide if it’s the right treatment for you Proven ways to help your loved one accept the treatment they need How to deal with suicidal thoughts and feelings How to help someone who is suicidal and save a life','[-0.014197349,0.0350679,-0.0572218,-0.017621847,-0.07353001,0.024530295,0.069710776,0.049046986,0.039923504,0.004697159,0.027197765,-0.00747359,-0.0694335,0.015053323,0.08580895,0.01744649,-0.024447763,0.011420168,-0.065185934,0.013309519,-0.0067039067,-0.032067154,0.016154272,-0.011875087,-0.012919344,0.07841259,0.008686973,-0.033827834,0.07395176,-0.00062608905,-0.027898367,0.068152264,-0.030890444,0.0018674948,-0.013293618,0.051999595,-0.020206442,0.096065395,-0.0034634643,-0.0060457033,-0.04379548,0.03698969,0.017315893,-0.094505616,0.027061472,-0.090020716,-0.1137463,0.020469328,0.0038024022,-0.10626112,-0.07829162,0.032888196,0.08511344,0.037797034,-0.049458243,-0.017136186,0.07995895,-0.0017465483,-0.03318029,0.01791825,0.017819744,0.035673514,-0.009292758,-0.051088765,0.09379195,0.049819406,-0.03910752,-0.031798013,0.050559558,-0.012582295,0.038126726,-0.006795964,-0.04365417,0.05794068,-0.032268245,0.024432134,-0.0036623245,-0.0036346437,0.055068605,0.058097593,0.03854183,0.080794506,0.065354295,-0.026707651,-0.00092498004,-0.0004285543,-0.029082367,0.06284769,-0.037394278,0.08105655,-0.02043621,0.0018295094,-0.06319256,-0.07715629,-0.044943497,-0.060499143,-0.018893486,-0.014757022,-0.04831138,0.029074768,0.055438656,-0.025128905,-0.00466305,0.061