(30353,'Personality, Social and Criminal Psychology',2,353,'What can we do about children who withdraw from loving care, or parents lost in the hurts of their own childhood? This book gathers 25 stories from 41 years in infant mental health, revealing how our earliest attachment experiences support or confound our later development. This essential guide to the youth transgender crisis argues social contagion is a key factor in the upsurge. It exposes the perils of medicalization—from puberty blockers to hormones—and offers a vital psychotherapeutic path for families.','[0.0314212,0.037029013,-0.050957207,0.010084277,-0.033194214,0.02122858,0.047066282,0.019799875,-0.02744118,0.011425781,0.11914075,-0.057656478,0.006472645,-0.052449066,0.007856015,0.015109486,0.03874864,-0.022897162,-0.10167065,-0.02961732,0.0015979847,-0.027708156,-0.03813689,-0.0014787489,-0.05546726,0.055421107,0.028805364,-0.03950908,0.100610025,-0.044529367,0.054072306,0.11592687,0.07754965,-0.07597071,-0.012468968,0.03977461,-0.023482367,-0.033721566,0.038240224,0.024246765,0.016929673,-0.0999571,-0.07846659,-0.090058,0.08460358,-0.04495269,-0.040489458,0.0017137483,0.036093462,-0.016826414,-0.060758248,0.051867764,-0.005478459,0.0041561667,-0.01199937,-0.12239596,-0.017111238,-0.01094002,-0.012450026,-0.025702214,0.0068029715,0.023018043,0.035254892,-0.011569617,0.12758905,-0.02041748,-0.07557034,-0.050576106,0.034339298,-0.04826514,0.036356196,-0.067850515,-0.0076146913,0.059429802,-0.099559925,-0.04821373,0.019128084,0.012838924,-0.013302109,-0.010735228,0.039219797,0.059606835,-0.00503756,0.0476394,-0.12761064,-0.01000545,-0.027162386,-0.004586083,-0.050221022,0.013056132,0.05199181,0.050156944,-0.07277747,-0.057650365,-0.034219943,0.018903915,-0.06695013,-0.033575214,0.0018928539,-0.011493641,-0.056512896,-0.0060802866,-0.044469144,-0.023005527,-0.047513705,-0.053983778,0.054353636,-0.08439086,0.041715227,0.038918152,-0.11920799,-0.038100537,-0.08772336,-0.06390942,0.05832431,-0.031741243,